{
  "texts": [
    "Alternatively, it may dilute the few real, positive biases with many null ones.",
    "Jin et al. (2021) argue and demonstrate that the benefit of task-adaptive pretraining depends on the task's causal direction.",
    "If the principle of independent causal mechanisms is also relevant to the fairness of pretraining on test set features, then our accuracy data may contain (for the sake of argument) positive evaluation biases for anti-causal tasks, and null biases for causal tasks.",
    "3 One way to analyze tasks is to sample from the posterior predictive distribution of the accuracy difference, and only average across subsamples:",
    "A more concise way is to perform a hypothesis test for each setting of m, n, and the LM type:"
  ]
}